  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (96ab913 2023-09-28T00:16:57.440609799Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI'm unable to switch forks created in forge when using `vm.selectFork(forkId)`. I get the following error:\r\n```The application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value\r\nLocation: crates/evm/src/executor/backend/mod.rs:663\r\n\r\nThis is a bug. Consider reporting it at https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry\r\n\r\n  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ SPANTRACE ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n\r\n   0: evm::cheatcodes::fork\r\n      at crates/evm/src/executor/inspector/cheatcodes/fork.rs:26\r\n   1: evm::cheatcodes::apply\r\n      at crates/evm/src/executor/inspector/cheatcodes/mod.rs:213\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\nAborted\r\n```\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n1. Do `forge init` and add the following text into `test/TestFork.t.sol`:\r\n```// SPDX-License-Identifier: NONE\r\npragma solidity >=0.8.0 <0.9.0;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Test.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract SimpleStorage {\r\n    uint256 public value;\r\n    function set(uint256 _value) external {\r\n        value = _value;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n/// @dev start anvil --port 35353\r\ncontract TestFork is Test {\r\n    function testFork() public {\r\n        uint256 forkId1 = vm.createFork(\"http://localhost:35353\");\r\n        uint256 forkId2 = vm.createFork(\"http://localhost:35353\");\r\n        vm.selectFork(forkId1);\r\n        SimpleStorage myContract = new SimpleStorage();\r\n        emit log_address(address(myContract));\r\n        vm.selectFork(forkId2);\r\n        SimpleStorage myContract2 = new SimpleStorage();\r\n        emit log_address(address(myContract2));\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n3. Start a local anvil node using `anvil --port 35353`\r\n4. In another terminal, run `forge test --mc TestFork`",
